<DOC><DOCNO> AP881019-0183 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-19-88 2018EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r p AM-DukakisBrochure     10-19 0241</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Dukakis Brochure,220</SECOND><HEAD>Illinois GOP Brochure Says Criminals Will Vote For Dukakis</HEAD><HEAD>With AM-Dukakis</HEAD><DATELINE>QUINCY, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Republican brochures denounced Wednesdayby Democratic presidential nominee Michael Dukakis were distributedby the Illinois GOP.   One of them bore the headline, ``All the Murderers and Rapistsand Drug Pushers and Child Molesters in Massachusetts Vote forMichael Dukakis,'' and the second one contained a similar messagebut bore a less inflammatory headline, ``Vote for Vice PresidentGeorge Bush for President.''   The first brochure alleged that convicts in Massachusetts havethe right to vote.   It cited Dukakis' opposition to the death penalty and hissupport for the controversial Massachusetts prison furlough program.   The brochure alleged that Dukakis has said that if the deathpenalty were reinstituted in Massachusetts by popular vote he wouldcommute death sentences.   It said the Massachusetts governor supports allowing convicts tovote and vetoed a bill to stop letting convicts out of prison onweekend passes.   The second brochure cited the Massachusetts furlough program andspecifically the case of Willie Horton, the furloughed convictedwho raped a Maryland woman. It said that convicted Illinoismass-murderer ``would be eligible for weekend passes''' under theMassachusetts program.   The material also touched on Social Security, saying that Bushwould never raid the trust fund as alleged by Dukakis andcontending that the Massachusetts governor ``has taken huge sums ofmoney from the Massachusetts pension funds to balance the statebudget.''</TEXT></DOC>